article.headline: Northern Iowa 79, Evansville 61
article.story: CEDAR FALLS, Iowa (AP) -- Grant Stout scored a career-high 24 points and Northern Iowa led for all but the first minute in beating Evansville 79-61 on Wednesday night. Eric Coleman and Chris Foster each added 12 points for the Panthers (15-7, 6-5 Missouri Valley), who had lost three of their previous four games. Northern Iowa shot 62 percent in building a 39-28 halftime lead and was never seriously challenged in the second half. Lucious Wagner's 15 points led Evansville (10-10, 4-8). No one else had more than nine for the Aces, who shot just 37.5 percent and committed 16 turnovers. Northern Iowa was able to get the ball inside consistently and outscored Evansville 34-20 in the paint. Ben Jacobson, Northern Iowa's leading scorer for the season, had the flu and was in the hospital as late as two hours before tipoff. Jacobson shot just 2-for-8 in scoring seven points but handed out six assists. Stout, a sophomore, scored 12 points in the first 5½ minutes to help the Panthers open a 16-8 lead. Jacobson's jumper with a minute left gave them their biggest lead of the opening half at 38-25. Northern Iowa held Evansville to one basket in the first 5 minutes of the second half while increasing the lead to 50-32. The Aces were never closer than 11 after that.
